## Design System

> Include this section only when the project has frontend code. Skip entirely for backend-only projects.

**Styling approach**: {{e.g., Tailwind CSS 3.4 with shadcn/ui primitives, CSS Modules with styled-components for theming, MUI v5 with custom theme}}

**Tokens & theme location**:
- {{e.g., `tailwind.config.ts` for spacing/colors/breakpoints}}
- {{e.g., `app/globals.css` defines CSS custom properties: --primary, --accent, --surface-1, --surface-2}}
- {{e.g., `src/styles/tokens.ts` exports the design tokens module}}

**Component library**: {{e.g., shadcn/ui in `components/ui/`, custom primitives in `components/primitives/`, MUI components imported from `@mui/material`}}

**Spacing scale**: {{e.g., 4px base — valid steps 4 8 12 16 24 32 48 64; expressed as Tailwind p-1 p-2 p-3 p-4 p-6 p-8 p-12 p-16}}

**Type scale**: {{e.g., Inter loaded via next/font; sizes text-xs to text-3xl from default Tailwind scale; weights 400/500/600/700}}

**Color tokens** (semantic — never use raw hex): {{e.g., --primary, --primary-foreground, --accent, --muted, --destructive, --surface-1; light/dark pairs in app/globals.css}}

**Breakpoints**: {{e.g., 375 mobile, 768 tablet, 1024 desktop, 1440 wide — Tailwind sm/md/lg/xl}}

**Design exemplars** (canonical components to mirror visually):
- {{e.g., `components/ui/button.tsx` — button states and variants}}
- {{e.g., `components/forms/text-field.tsx` — input states, error display, label rhythm}}
- {{e.g., `app/(dashboard)/projects/page.tsx` — page-level layout, density, hierarchy}}

**State conventions**: {{e.g., hover via `hover:bg-accent`, focus via `focus-visible:ring-2 ring-ring`, disabled via `disabled:opacity-50 disabled:pointer-events-none`, loading uses `<Spinner />` from primitives, empty states use `<EmptyState />` template}}

**Accessibility baseline**: {{e.g., WCAG AA contrast minimum, semantic HTML before ARIA, all interactive elements keyboard accessible, focus-visible rings on every focusable element}}

**Aesthetic direction** (for greenfield work only — leave blank for matured projects): {{e.g., "minimal/editorial" or "warm/organic" — if set, frontend-agent uses this when there's no existing convention to anchor to. If blank, frontend-agent stays on the universal baseline.}}

